fields.job_description:
I interned for the Office of Enrollment Management and Business Intelligence. Some of my responsibilities included In-Person Training, Training Documentation, Use Cases, etc. 

Improve system security and prevent unauthorized access to sensitive student data.

The other aspect of the role was to provide salesforce support, knowledge, and troubleshooting to clients such as the Mason Student Service Center. The great part about the role was that I would learn new things every few weeks.

I was responsible to create a safe and secure environment for 400 residents in the community which included peer-to-peer conflict resolution, creating and reporting incidents with detailed narratives.
Assisting with the implementation and execution of the residential education initiatives in the community. Respond to student concerns and crisis situations when necessary such as sexual assault, suicidal ideation; and engage with HRL and campus resources to provide support.
fields.employer: Housing and Residence Life | Patrick O' Connor

fields.Name: The Black Knights
fields.description:
The Black Knights were my senior design team name. In this project, we created a simple and scalable solution for a fashion business based out of Georgia. The project was 100% remote and our web solutions were deployed to increase the business revenue. The solutions saved the client an upward of 10K/ year.

Here is the client's website: https://alexblaque.com/

fields.Name: Study Mason
fields.description:
worked in a team as part of Mason Summer Entrepreneurship Accelerator to evaluate our business idea and hypothesize. We learned multiple SDLC methodologies to implement the business idea and conducted 100+ customer discovery interviews with stakeholders including college students, professors, and offices to create a mobile application that enables students to find a study partner.
The Result: over 75 percent of students and professors interviewed supported the business idea.
fields.Mentor:
David L Powell
The principal of DLPIBC, LLC (International Sales and Marketing)

fields.Name: Study Panda
fields.description: Creating a rapidly deployable Django web application to help facilitate student interactions with peers to improve study habits and understand the study patterns. The idea was initially limited to George Mason University but now is expanding to all large public and private universities as COVID-19 has changed the way we learn. Currently working with a team of 6 software engineers to build and deploy.
fields.Mentor: Karen Livingston. Associate Director, Entrepreneurship Programs, GMU
